column35: Discuss agreements on notifying board of pending need for comments: i.e.In accordance with this agreement, the lease agreement is scheduled to be renewed on March 17th, 2021 (60 days prior to the expiration of the current agreement).  The new agreement would increase the monthly lease amount by 10% per month ($300.00) in accordance with the initial agreement outside of purchasing the property prior to February 17th, 2021.    The new lease would be a maximum of $3,300 per month.  No agreements as in the ByLaws would be altered by the renewal of this lease agreement.    There are 10 days of open comment prior to this renewal taking place in automatically.  After such time, comments will be closed and the agreement will be renewed without exception." My request is that the BOD is notified verbally and in our text and team chat when something important like this is on the floor.

column35: I spoke with my colleagues and they said that the student, your daughter, and any other students who are having problems, need to do the following. If they have already done a step in the list, then they should go on to the next. 1.	Speak with the instructor to see if they will work with them regarding the issues. 2.	If that does not bring about a fair resolution, speak with Shereen Schultz, the course coordinator. at6752@wayne.edu 3.	If that does not work, then submit the following form. https://clas.wayne.edu/math/students/feedback/form Without doing that process, the student's concerns will not go up the chain, if they want them to. I hope this helps.  Chris
